io.github.pr0methean.betterrandom.util.spliterator

Class LongSupplierSpliterator

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.pr0methean.betterrandom.util.spliterator.AbstractSupplierSpliterator<LongSupplier,LongConsumer,LongSupplierSpliterator>
      • io.github.pr0methean.betterrandom.util.spliterator.LongSupplierSpliterator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Spliterator<Long>, Spliterator.OfLong, Spliterator.OfPrimitive<Long,LongConsumer,Spliterator.OfLong>

    public class LongSupplierSpliterator
extends AbstractSupplierSpliterator<LongSupplier,LongConsumer,LongSupplierSpliterator>
implements Spliterator.OfLong
    An unordered, concurrent Spliterator.OfLong that invokes a LongSupplier to get its values. Has a preset size if it isn't the result of a AbstractSupplierSpliterator.trySplit(), but shares its total size with the other splits if it is.
    Author:
    Chris Hennick

    • Method Detail

      • internalSplit

        protected LongSupplierSpliterator internalSplit(AtomicLong remaining,
                                                AtomicLong splitsRemaining)
        Description copied from class: AbstractSupplierSpliterator
        Splits off a new instance that uses the same Supplier, and shares its counts of remaining items and remaining permitted splits with this one. Doesn't decrement the number of remaining permitted splits (that's done in AbstractSupplierSpliterator.trySplit()). Should wrap a constructor that ultimately calls AbstractSupplierSpliterator(remaining, splitsRemaining, supplier, false).
        Specified by:
        internalSplit in class AbstractSupplierSpliterator<LongSupplier,LongConsumer,LongSupplierSpliterator>
        Parameters:
        remaining - An AtomicLong (shared between splits) that stores how many more items will be output by AbstractSupplierSpliterator.tryAdvance(Object).
        splitsRemaining - An AtomicLong (shared between splits) that stores how many more times the AbstractSupplierSpliterator.trySplit() command will return non-null.
        Returns:
        a descendant spliterator.

      • internalSupplyAndAccept

        protected void internalSupplyAndAccept(LongConsumer action)
        Description copied from class: AbstractSupplierSpliterator
        Supplies the next output value to action. Should be equivalent to action.accept(supplier.get()).
        Specified by:
        internalSupplyAndAccept in class AbstractSupplierSpliterator<LongSupplier,LongConsumer,LongSupplierSpliterator>
        Parameters:
        action - the consumer that will receive the next output value if there is one.
